by there, there

00:25:29.480 --> 00:25:35.060
were cans and plastic
bags everywhere.

00:25:35.060 --> 00:25:37.060
Duh, you smart guy.

00:25:37.060 --> 00:25:39.290
Stop the car.

00:25:39.290 --> 00:25:44.090
I started to explain to them
that they couldn't do this.

00:25:44.090 --> 00:25:46.070
It's awful.

00:25:46.070 --> 00:25:47.730
You live in Amazonas.

00:25:47.730 --> 00:25:53.780
A can, a plastic
bag, that's not good.

00:25:53.780 --> 00:25:55.250
And they didn't understand.

00:25:55.250 --> 00:25:58.730
They became upset with me.

00:25:58.730 --> 00:26:02.280
So the temperature
started to rise up,

00:26:02.280 --> 00:26:05.730
and I became not comfortable.

00:26:05.730 --> 00:26:08.910
And one of the oldest men
faced me and said, Alex,

00:26:08.910 --> 00:26:13.810
it's your fault.

00:26:13.810 --> 00:26:16.070
I said, sir, sorry.

00:26:16.070 --> 00:26:19.750
I started to send food for
your grandchildren, which

00:26:19.750 --> 00:26:24.460
have almost the same age
that your youngest son,

00:26:24.460 --> 00:26:27.210
and you try to blame me.

00:26:27.210 --> 00:26:31.890
And he answered
almost like this.

00:26:31.890 --> 00:26:34.420
Packaging of fruits is the skin.

00:26:34.420 --> 00:26:37.230
Packaging of fish is the scales.

00:26:37.230 --> 00:26:39.530
Packaging of one animal is fur.

00:26:39.530 --> 00:26:41.390
I throw away.

00:26:41.390 --> 00:26:47.080
At the first moment, the
skin looks very violent.

00:26:47.080 --> 00:26:53.250
But who was sending the cans
and the plastic bags to them?

00:26:53.250 --> 00:26:58.200
That was the day that I
realized that maybe as a chef,

00:26:58.200 --> 00:27:05.840
I can handle the food
chain, but not the food web.

00:27:08.880 --> 00:27:13.810
That was the day that
I realized that this

00:27:13.810 --> 00:27:20.580
is an interdisciplinary
thing, and I

00:27:20.580 --> 00:27:24.980
might should learn and be
supported by anthropologists,

00:27:24.980 --> 00:27:27.950
by sociologists, by
different disciplines.

